AnimateDiff Group:
- Set for AnimateDiff LCM

Face Detailer Group:
- Face detailer can be used for hands or body as well with few adjustments
- Two options in order to detect face. Option 2 goes faster but it is less accurate.
- Don't forget to connect Mask to Grow Mask with Blur node when you change option
- Mask can be adjusted with crop_size_mult parameter in Batch Crop From Mask Advanced node
- Grow Mask with Blur Node is useful to make your mask bigger or smaller (negative values are allowed)
- Use the viewers to adjust and debbug your mask
- The node Impact Image Info gives you the dimensions of the mask and final output. Useful for debugging
- if an error: "stack expects each tensor to be equal size" appears. Lower the decay factor in Grow mask with blur node. 0.95 should work.

Video Group:
- Set your Number of frames.
- Set Nth frames if you want to go faster
- Use CR Aspect Ratio to resize
Do I really need to explain these groups ???

Upscaler Group:
- A little tool to allow you to choose which upscaler model is the best.
- Download them on:https://openmodeldb.info/
- SD Ultimate Group is for short videos or high GPU. Personally, I'm a proletarian ai artist and cannot afford that kind of nodes. But rich people with more than 24GB gpu can. Don't forget to connect the output

Sampler + HiRes Group:
- Better, Faster, Stronger.
- HiRes Fix is done with NNLatent Upscale. Change the scale to go faster.
- Small tips. Change the connection of the node applying tile CN in connecting it to the first sampler or one of the ControlNet node. I didn't do it because all ControlNets will apply and that takes more time.

Prompt Group:
- AnimateDiffLCM lora is loaded here
- v3_sd15_adapter may be removed but I think it helps with video consistency

IpAdapter Group:
- Download Mask here:
https://i.ibb.co/kmY66Kp/parallax-mask.png
- Allows you to change the background or Foreground easily

ControlNet Group:
- Bypass Group Nodes with right click
- I didn't use ControlNet Stack or fancy nodes because it slows the process
